			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Banning or suspension for Dmitry - community discussion
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1497682">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Yesterday evening Dmitry revealed the identity of a number of people who had reported posts in a public thread and publicly insulted them, calling them bitches. He also sent a PM to at least one person who made a report calling them a pussy. (I have now had this confirmed).<br />
<br />
While I am aware that some people believe that reports should be public, we currently work under a system in which people have an expectation of privacy for their reports. Further, members of the board are entitled when making reports to be treated civilly by the moderation team.<br />
<br />
Accordingly I am invoking the clause in the moderation guidelines that allows for a poster to be suspended or banned based on a vote from the moderation team. I will be asking the moderators to vote on the following questions:<br />
<br />
Should Dmitry be permanently banned? (yes/no)<br />
<br />
Should Dmitry be suspended? (yes/no)<br />
<br />
If you vote yes to a suspension, how long should the suspension be?<br />
<br />
The moderation guidelines provide no procedure for removing moderator privileges. However, rather than simply make a unilateral decision I will also be asking the moderators the following question:<br />
<br />
Should Dmitry be stripped of his moderator status until the next election? (yes/no)<br />
<br />
Feedback from the community on all these issues is actively sought in this thread.<br />
<br />
Normally I would also give an day for the vote to occur. At this point due to my impending loss of reliable internet I will have to investigate alternate arrangements before announcing this. It will certainly occur before the end of the week.<br />
<br />
Finally, I ask that we not derail this thread into a discussion of the appropriateness of the thread title edit I made earlier this week. I acknowledge and indeed defend Dmitry's right to disagree vehemently and publicly with me about that matter, and I do not think that my decisions are immune to criticism, discussion, or reversal. However the possible incorrectness of my decision there does not justify Dmitry's treatment of posters reporting threads they believed to be in violation of the rules.<br />
<br />
Update: I have made arrangements for the mods to cast their votes by <b>midnight PST Thursday</b> -- Nadiar will be posting the outcome and executing it in my absence.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
