		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Banning or suspension for Dmitry - community discussion
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1497771">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Should Dmitry be permanently banned? Yes perma ban<br />
<br />
Should Dmitry be stripped of his moderator status until the next election? Is there any question at all about this?  He also needs to never have those mod powers ever again, election or no.<br />
<br />
He started the day after his suspension was up trolling and doing the exact same thing he did to get that suspension in the first place.  If that was it, I wouldn't be so bothered, but after that he crossed a very visible line.  He abused his mod powers and spent hours on end creating an endless stream of filth in every single one of his threads.  It was hatespeach spam and a complete disruption of the entire board.<br />
<br />
Do you really think a suspension will work after what he just did after a suspension?<br />
<br />
He knew exactly what he was doing.  He knew that this would get him a ban and went even further with his insults and abusing mod powers.<br />
<br />
I know if I did a fraction of what he did as someone who spends most of my time lurking that the mods and admins would have no problem whatsoever giving me the banhammer.  Why should it be any less for a prominent member who abused his mod powers and spammed this board for hours with hate speech and trolling.  Not only that but personally harassing bard members who did their job and reported it.<br />
<br />
A lot of people have been banned for doing far less.  He needs to spend at least a year away from here, and judging how this board deals with bans this would work out perfectly.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
